# File: bigcam/usr/share/biglinux/bigcam/ui/about_dialog.py, line: 39
msgid ""
"The universal webcam control center for Linux.\n"
"\n"
"BigCam was born as a small shell script so that Rafael Ruscher could use his Canon Rebel T3 as a "
"webcam during live streams about BigLinux. That humble hack, written by Rafael and Barnabé di "
"Kartola, evolved from a Bash bridge between gPhoto2 and FFmpeg into a full GTK4/Adwaita application "
"with live preview, multi-backend camera support (V4L2, gPhoto2, libcamera, PipeWire, IP cameras, "
"smartphones), real-time OpenCV effects, virtual camera output, photo and video capture, and 29 "
"languages."
msgstr ""
"Le centre de contrôle de webcam universel pour Linux.\n"
"\n"
"BigCam est né comme un petit script shell afin que Rafael Ruscher puisse utiliser son Canon Rebel "
"T3 comme webcam lors de diffusions en direct sur BigLinux. Ce humble hack, écrit par Rafael et "
"Barnabé di Kartola, a évolué d'un pont Bash entre gPhoto2 et FFmpeg en une application complète "
"GTK4/Adwaita avec aperçu en direct, support multi-backend pour les caméras (V4L2, gPhoto2, "
"libcamera, PipeWire, caméras IP, smartphones), effets OpenCV en temps réel, sortie de caméra "
"virtuelle, capture de photos et de vidéos, et 29 langues."
